    "summary": "Passionate Software Developer who has a demonstrated history working for the Internet industry in multidisciplinary projects, with a Master of Science (MSc) in Electrical and Computer Engineering from Instituto Superior T\u00e9cnico in Lisbon, having specialized in the topic of network routing protocols.\n\nExperienced in various types of web backend development, using technologies and frameworks such as Perl, Java, MySQL, Git, and C++, and having become familiar with MacOS, Unix and Windows operating systems. Worked in a multitude of software development projects, ranging from secure storage systems to managing message-exchanging APIs with sensitive data.\n\nStrong professional in the field of academic research, in the area of telecommunications and network protocols, having worked intensively on the topic during 1 year. Co-authored a paper, and participated on the ACM SIGCOMM '15 conference in London. Developed proficiency in LaTeX, C, Matlab, algorithm design and analysis.\n\nCommitment to exceptional performance when involved in enthusiastic projects, as shown from merit scholarships, and open willingness for constant self-development, as seen from the Entrepreneurship Lean LaunchPad initiative.\n\nOther interests include writing, storytelling, cinema, and traveling, as well as all types of team-building events. Very invested in solid communication skills and teamwork, and unstoppable when motivated!",
